Element-body whitespace baseline. These renders are the reference that
control-flow bodies must match for INTERIOR whitespace. Element bodies already
behave correctly; this pins the reference.

Note: gsx's wsnorm collapses EVERY interior whitespace run to a single space
(s4: `{a}   -   {b}` -> `x - y`). This is a deliberate, pre-existing gsx design
(docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-21-gsx-whitespace-model-design.md) that diverges
from React/JSX, which preserves an intra-line multi-space run verbatim (`x   -   y`)
and leaves collapsing to the browser. s1/s3 (single space) and newline-dropping
DO match React; multi-space collapse is gsx-specific. The invariant THIS case
pins is element-body behavior; control-flow bodies must match it exactly.
-- input.gsx --
package views

component Base(a, b string) {
	<div id="s1">{a} - end</div>
	<div id="s3">{a} {b}</div>
	<div id="s4">{a}   -   {b}</div>
}
-- invoke --
Base("x", "y")
-- diagnostics.golden --
-- render.golden --
<div id="s1">x - end</div><div id="s3">x y</div><div id="s4">x - y</div>
-- generated.x.go.golden --
